value.text:
Update: App Passwords no longer have access to your invite codes, to ensure that third-party tools cannot claim your invite codes without your awareness.

Please only login to third-party tools that you trust, and always use an App Password (a temporary solution until we implement OAuth). 🧵

record.text:
❓ Q: What permissions do App Passwords have?

💬 A: They have most of the same abilities as the user's account password, but they're restricted from destructive actions such as account deletion. They are also restricted from creating additional app passwords and from viewing invite codes.

Update: App Passwords no longer have access to your invite codes, to ensure that third-party tools cannot claim your invite codes without your awareness.

Please only login to third-party tools that you trust, and always use an App Password (a temporary solution until we implement OAuth). 🧵

❓ Q: What are App Passwords?

💬 A: App Passwords are revokable passwords you can use to login to third-party tools. You can generate them at Settings > Advanced > App Passwords.

If you notice spam accounts, you can report it to us, and any additional context you add helps us investigate!
Let’s talk about how we use invite trees to track spam bots on Bluesky 🧵:

When we investigate spam networks, we use invite trees to identify where they came from. Often, an entire network of spam bots comes from the same invite tree. This makes it easier for us to track down and ban these accounts.

📢 1.49 is here! It has some big updates to the Web app.

• Threads now sort replies by likes
• Fixes to the sync of moderation settings (adult content) between devices
• Improvements to the logged out UI on web
• The web app now correctly resizes for narrower screens
• Additional bugfixes, of course
If you have friends looking for an invite, they can sign up for the waitlist at bsky.app. We email thousands of invites per day, and existing users receive invites periodically.

We highly discourage invite sales and can’t verify their authenticity.

About the Likes tab:

Likes are public on Bluesky. We’ve added a Likes tab to your own profile so you can quickly find past posts you’ve liked, but we chose not to show that tab on other users’ profiles.

Those likes can still be accessed by APIs, so other apps may show them.

record.text:
❓ Q: Will this affect me as a dev?

💬 A: This affects you if you're doing commit-aware repo sync, i.e. if you've ever passed earliest or latest to com.atproto.sync.getRepo or explicitly check repo version. 

For most projects subscribed to the firehose, like custom feeds, you shouldn't be affected.

record.text: `deleteAccount` is rate limited by IP, 50 requests/5 minute

To improve network stability & security, we're adding some application rate limits for actions like resetting your password.

This update should *not* affect your experience of this service. 

More details threaded for devs below 🧵:
sounds dumb but did you rate limit the request delete account?
You shouldn't notice any difference with posting! These updates will help make the service more secure & reliable.

We also now return rate limit headers on each response so devs can dynamically adapt to them.

The routes with more aggressive rate limits include endpoints like `updateHandle` and `resetPassword` to prevent exploits. But if you're unexpectedly affected, let us know!

record.text:
Some more details for devs:

The App View is the piece of our federation architecture that gives you all your views of data, such as profiles and threads. 

Initially, we served all of these requests from our PDS, but now we've started proxying them to the App View, which affected some handles.

value.text:
One part of our upgraded infrastructure may affect your profile.

If you see your handle now says “Invalid handle,” please reverify it by navigating to Settings > Change my handle > Type in your current handle > Verify DNS Record > Update.

(Basically, update to the same handle.)
